      "type": "text",
      "name": "intro_text",
      "value": "This app has two entry points on the home page.",
      "style_list": "margin-top: -4px;"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "name": "intro_text",
      "value": "**1. Topics**\n\nWe dividied early mathematics into topics from all the math standards. Each topic has a description with teaching tips. It also has links to a Glossary and a Resource Finder. There are two ways to see the topics.\n\n**Hierarchical View** The topics are listed by themes which are organiized into strands. This is also the place to choose the standard to use for viewing topics throughout the app.\n\n**Learning Pathways** This presents the topics as part of learning pathways.\n\n**2. Resources**\n* **Resource Finder** – Lists resources for a topic or group of topics\n* **Instructional Routines** – Groups of 1-10-minute tasks\n* **Rich Tasks** – 1-3-lesson activities going more deeply into a topic\n* **Puzzles**\n* **Games**\n* **Storybooks**\n* **Glossary** – Definitions and explanations of math terminology",
      "style_list": "margin-top: -4px;"
    },
